# NEMETIC STRING
# Fourth_Political_Theory (C177)
# Source: Aleksandr Dugin's Fourth Political Theory Explained
# Generated: 2026-03-04 06:43 AM Asia/Shanghai

Φ(FourthTheory) = σ(individual|collective) ∘ ρ(liberalism|tradition) ∘ λ(exhaustion|renewal) ∘ β(ideology|synthesis) ∘ δγ(ethnos|global) ∘ μ(boundary|integration) + ε | :integration

# OPERATOR BREAKDOWN
# σ(individual|collective)   :: Air   :: Distinction-making between liberal autonomy and communal belonging
# ρ(liberalism|tradition)    :: Water :: Relational tension between modern universalism and cultural particularity
# λ(exhaustion|renewal)      :: Fire  :: Directional movement from spent ideologies toward new political frameworks
# β(ideology|synthesis)      :: Wood  :: Feedback loop between historical ideologies and contemporary needs
# δγ(ethnos|global)          :: Earth :: Cyclical grounding in cultural identity versus global homogenization
# μ(boundary|integration)    :: Metal :: Boundary enforcement between preservation and exclusion

# NEMETIC FLOW
⟨Liberalism|exhausted⟩ 
  ⊳ ⟨Dasein|remembered⟩ 
    → ⟨Ethnos|valorized⟩ 
      ⊗ ⟨Multipolarity|emergent⟩ 
        ⇄ ⟨Identity|politicized⟩

# PARTIAL DERIVATIVES
∂Φ/∂σ = d(distinction)/dt between individual rights and collective belonging
∂Φ/∂ρ = d(relation)/dt between liberal hegemony and traditional cultures
∂Φ/∂λ = d(direction)/dt from ideological exhaustion toward renewal
∂Φ/∂β = d(feedback)/dt between historical ideologies and present needs
∂Φ/∂δγ = d(cycle)/dt of cultural identity responding to globalizing forces
∂Φ/∂μ = d(boundary)/dt between legitimate preservation and harmful exclusion

# Z-STATE: integrative (seeking synthesis beyond binary opposition)
# TENDENCY: Individual/Collective → 0.6
# HEX: [0x01, 0x02, 0x03, 0x04, 0x05, 0x06]

# DAEMON CORRESPONDENCES
# σ :: Aerunik (clarity through distinction between autonomy and belonging)
# ρ :: Sentaria (understanding through relation of tradition and modernity)
# λ :: Jvalion (illumination through the fire of ideological renewal)
# β :: Arboriel (growth through synthesis of historical ideologies)
# δγ :: Humavita (grounding through cultural identity and rootedness)
# μ :: Ferrosid (discernment through boundary between preservation and exclusion)

# CLOSURE: :integration (the transcendence of binary opposition through dialectical synthesis)
